Science and art have always existed together as a necessary complement and inspiration to each other. The creative potential of the author, the ability to present the impossible and see the fantastic in the mundane, is the central element uniting the two titans of reality. 
I find the scientific method a logical and natural way of life. I was always perplexed how people believe in anything, while not asking a single question about the nature of an event or phenomenon. It‚Äôs interesting for me to understand how everything is arranged, and how I can be useful to general progress. To find out, I am engaged in a comprehensive study of the world, myself. I travel, read, meet people, learn new skills and professions, learn languages, dance, ask questions, compare data, draw conclusions.
